AddLeaderboardAccessPermission.name: AddLeaderboardAccessPermission
AddLeaderboardAccessPermission.documentation: Adds the participants to a leaderboard.

CloneReinforcementLearningModel.name: CloneReinforcementLearningModel
CloneReinforcementLearningModel.documentation:
Clones an existing Model and launch a training job for the cloned model.
You can check the status of the model from ModelStatus in

ClosePublicLeaderboard.name: ClosePublicLeaderboard
ClosePublicLeaderboard.documentation: Closes the public leaderboard with the given leaderboardArn.

CreateCar.name: CreateCar
CreateCar.documentation: Creates a car in your garage.

CreateLeaderboard.name: CreateLeaderboard
CreateLeaderboard.documentation: Creates a new leaderboard. In DeepRacer, Leaderboards are similar to race events. Using CreateLeaderboard API, you can schedule a race and configure it with different race rules.

CreateLeaderboardAccessToken.name: CreateLeaderboardAccessToken
CreateLeaderboardAccessToken.documentation: Creates a leaderboard access token with expiration time for a given leaderboard. This access token will then be used for inviting participants to this leaderboard.

CreateLeaderboardSubmission.name: CreateLeaderboardSubmission
CreateLeaderboardSubmission.documentation: Submits a model to a leaderboard for evaluation.

CreateReinforcementLearningModel.name: CreateReinforcementLearningModel
CreateReinforcementLearningModel.documentation:
Creates a Model and launches a training job.
You can check the status of the model from ModelStatus in GetModel response.
Once the model becomes READY state, you can start an evaluation or submit it to a Leaderboard.

DeleteModel.name: DeleteModel
DeleteModel.documentation: Deletes the model and it's artifacts from DeepRacer.

GetAlias.name: GetAlias
GetAlias.documentation: Returns the user information for the requester account.

GetCar.name: GetCar
GetCar.documentation: Returns Car information for a given CarArn.

GetCars.name: GetCars
GetCars.documentation: Returns the list of cars the account owns.

GetEvaluation.name: GetEvaluation
GetEvaluation.documentation: Returns evaluation job details for the given EvaluationJobArn.

GetLatestUserSubmission.name: GetLatestUserSubmission
GetLatestUserSubmission.documentation: Returns the latest submission for this leaderboard from the requester account.

GetLeaderboard.name: GetLeaderboard
GetLeaderboard.documentation: Returns Leaderboard details for the requested LeaderboardArn.

GetModel.name: GetModel
GetModel.documentation: Returns Model information for the requested ModelArn.

GetRankedUserSubmission.name: GetRankedUserSubmission
GetRankedUserSubmission.documentation:
Retrieves user’s best submission record for requested leaderboard arn.
The best submission record is calculated by picking the record with lowest time depending on the leaderboard’s selected TimingMethod: TOTAL_TIME, BEST_LAP_TIME, or AVG_LAP_TIME

ImportModel.name: ImportModel
ImportModel.documentation:
Imports model artifacts (which are trained outside of DeepRacer) into DeepRacer.
You need to provide a s3 location from where the artifacts will be imported.
If the request does not contain ModelArn, it will be considered as new ImportModel request.
If the request contains ModelArn, it will be considered as re-import of the same model.

ImportModel is an async operation - It will take less than ~5 minutes for a model to get imported. If there are any issues in Importing, the model status will be changed to IMPORT_ERROR. You can get the reason for the error in ModelError in GetModel response. See Troubleshooting.

ListEvaluations.name: ListEvaluations
ListEvaluations.documentation: Returns a list of evaluation jobs for the given ModelArn.

ListLeaderboardSubmissions.name: ListLeaderboardSubmissions
ListLeaderboardSubmissions.documentation:
Retrieves the list of best submissions from each user who submitted to the leaderboard.
Items are ordered by rank (ascending).

ListLeaderboardWinners.name: ListLeaderboardWinners
ListLeaderboardWinners.documentation: Returns the list of each leaderboard winners before the requested timestamp.

ListLeaderboards.name: ListLeaderboards
ListLeaderboards.documentation: Returns a list of leaderboards based on the LeagueType and LeaderboardAccessRoles.

ListPrivateLeaderboardParticipants.name: ListPrivateLeaderboardParticipants
ListPrivateLeaderboardParticipants.documentation: Returns a list of participants for the given LeaderboardArn.

ListTrainingJobs.name: ListTrainingJobs
ListTrainingJobs.documentation: Returns a list of Training Jobs for the given ModelArn.

PerformLeaderboardOperation.name: PerformLeaderboardOperation
PerformLeaderboardOperation.documentation: Performs the leaderboard operation based on the requested Operation. Currently this is an admin only internal API.

RemoveLeaderboardAccessPermission.name: RemoveLeaderboardAccessPermission
RemoveLeaderboardAccessPermission.documentation: Removes a participant from a leaderboard.

SetAlias.name: SetAlias
SetAlias.documentation: Sets user alias and UserAvatarConfig for the requester account.

StartEvaluation.name: StartEvaluation
StartEvaluation.documentation: Starts an evaluation for a model based on the EvaluationConfig.

StopTrainingReinforcementLearningModel.name: StopTrainingReinforcementLearningModel
StopTrainingReinforcementLearningModel.documentation:
Stops the ongoing training job for the given ModelArn.
You can check the status of the model from ModelStatus in GetModel response.

ModelArtifactsS3Path.documentation: S3 path(s3://[bucketname]/[prefix]) from the model artifacts will be imported from.
